result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

ADDRESS INFO for Jay M Anderson
Current: 115 E Miner Ave. Apt #4, Ladysmith, WI 54848   (Effective: 01-25-2016)
Prior: 315 Worden Ave. E, Ladysmith, WI 54848

Defendant Jay M Anderson in court with attorney Annette M Barna.  James Jay Rennicke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Heard along with 15CM133, 16CM14.  Case settlement has been reached in all cases.  Court recites case settlement into the court record.  Court instructs on plea questionnaire/waiver of rights.  DE will enter a plea of NC to amended count in 13CM91, and Ct 3  in 15CM133.  Ct's 1,2 in 15CM133 and 16CM14 will be DRI.  Court will accept and find the DE guilty.  Court accepts the recommendations of the parties.  DE has indicated he will be moving out of State to MN.  Atty asking for expunction if all court obligations have been paid.  The court will order expunction upon successful completion of both cases, and no further criminal convictions on record after today's date within the next year.
No contact with Danielle D Hendrix-Blue (DOB 5-24-1970) Do not go to Krist Oil
